@startuml Process Monitoring - Unilateral Down Signal

title Process Monitoring: Receive DOWN Signals (Unilateral)

participant Watcher as watcher
participant "ProcMonitor" as monitor
participant "Target Proc" as target
participant Handler as handler

== Monitor Installation ==

watcher -> monitor: monitor(target, downHandler)
note right of monitor
  Returns MonitorRef
  Handler will be invoked on target crash
  Does NOT kill the watcher
end note
monitor -> target: install DOWN callback
monitor --> watcher: return MonitorRef

watcher -> watcher: continue running
target -> target: continue processing

== Normal Target Termination ==

target -> target: exit message loop normally
target -> handler: downHandler.accept(null)
note right of handler
  null = normal exit
  Runs on target's thread context
  Must not block (brief callback)
end note

== Target Crash ==

target -> target: exception in handler
target -> target: lastError = exception
target -> target: exit message loop

target -> handler: downHandler.accept(exception)
note right of handler
  non-null = abnormal exit
  Handler logs/records the crash
  Watcher is NOT affected
end note

watcher -> watcher: unaffected! still running
note right of watcher
  Unlike ProcLink:
  - Monitoring is unilateral
  - Watcher does not crash
  - Does not receive exit signal as message

  Use case: health checks
  Can demonitor() if monitor no longer needed
end note

== Demonitoring ==

watcher -> monitor: demonitor(monitorRef)
monitor -> target: remove DOWN callback
note right of watcher
  If target crashes now,
  no DOWN signal will be sent
end note
